crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ELF binary is a sophisticated multi-functional backdoor and botnet agent. Key malicious behaviors include: 1) Persistent background execution via daemonization and self-replication (copying /proc/self/exe to /tmp/ and executing the copy); 2) Anti-forensics by unsetting the HISTFILE environment variable to prevent command logging; 3) System reconnaissance gathering OS version, hostname, and networking details; 4) Interactive reverse shell capability using pseudo-terminals (openpty) and /bin/sh; and 5) Encrypted command-and-control (C2) communication utilizing complex symmetric cryptographic routines (likely AES or similar). Notable IOCs include the hardcoded strings 'r0st@#$' and 'VMware#@!Station', as well as suspicious file paths like 'tmp/.llock' and 'usr/include/sdfwex.h'.
